Description
Application
 
Edge
Class which represents an edge (link) between two nodes.
EdgeRepository
This interface allows for communication with the PostgreSQL database.
EdgeService
Class which allows for access to various methods which will alter the data within the 'edges' table of the database.
Graph
Class which represents a graph.
GraphAPIController
Class which represents the controller used to handle API routes.
GraphController
Class which represents the controller used to display pages, as well as access models via their respective services.
GraphService
Class which allows for access to both NodeService and EdgeService, as well as ensuring that the static XML is parsed so that a Graph can be produced.
Node
Class which represents a node.
NodeRepository
This interface allows for communication with the PostgreSQL database.
NodeService
Class which allows for access to various methods which will alter the data within the 'nodes' table of the database.
ShortestPath
Class which represents data pertaining to the shortest path.
Timer
Class which allows for timing.
XMLParsingUtility
Class which allows for XML data to be parsed into a readable format that can be used to create nodes and edges.
